textBox.richText: I had yet another dream last night. This one was worse than the other one. The details for this dream are a bit fuzzy, but the main epicentral point here was that… we had finally gotten together. I don’t remember why or how it happened, but it did. I think this took place in some fictional dorm hallway landing, but that’s irrelevant to the point. I remember being so happy too… I thought things were finally falling into place… only to then wake up and realize the sad fact that it was indeed a dream and to remember how the condition of things actually stood in reality. Why must my subconscious agonize me like this? It’s bad enough I have to make efforts to deal with it IRL-style, and now I’m being plagued with fallacies about everything “working out” while I sleep. Nuurgruhh… Fuck me.
